Getting help and identifying valid targets
------------------------------------------

If you run _Middlemac_ with an invalid target, with no parameters, or with the
`-h` or `--help` switch, _Middlemac_ will display its documentation.


Middlemac command signature
---------------------------

`./middlemac.rb TARGET... | all  [--verbose | -v] [--quiet | -q] [--help | -h] [--server | -s]`

`TARGET...`
 : One or more valid targets as configured in `config.rb`. If you specify a mix
   of valid and invalid targets, _Middlemac_ will fail with an explanation.
   
`all`
 : The `all` target will build  all of the targets that are configured in
   `config.rb`. If specified with valid targets, the valid targets will be
   ignored in the command, but built as they are included in `all`. However
   `all` specified with invalid targets will fail with an explanation.
   
`--verbose`
`-v`
 : Executes _Middleman_ in verbose mode for each build target.
 
`--quiet`
`-q`
 : Silences _Middleman_ output, even if --verbose is specified.
 
